// //             engText: "Once upon a time, in the vast, ice-covered polar regions, lived a cute and brave penguin. His name was Penguin Pingo. Pingo, with his bright white belly and cute blue hat, was loved by everyone. Pingo's biggest dream was to discover other creatures living in the polar regions and make friends with them. One day, a ship stopped near the glaciers where Pingo lived. There were children who got off this ship. The children had come to explore the animals and nature in the polar regions, and when they met Pingo, they immediately became friends. One of these children was named Elsa, and the other was Jack. Elsa said, \"Hello Pingo! We came here to discover the animals and nature in the polar regions.\" Pingo smiled, \"Great! I want to introduce you to my wonderful friends here. Come on, let's go on an adventure together!\" First, Pingo took the children on a walk over the glaciers. After a while, a polar bear with white fur and cute black eyes appeared. Pingo said, \"This is my friend Boris, he is a very kind bear.\" Boris said, \"Welcome! The polar regions are a magical place. Here, we always help each other,\" and waved his big paws to the children. Elsa and Jack loved Boris's huge but friendly appearance. Then, they encountered a family of seals. The mother seal was playing on the ice with her pups. Pingo said, \"This is my seal family. They are excellent swimmers.\" Jack watched in admiration, \"Wow! They swim so fast.\" As they continued their walk, the sky began to darken, and the northern lights colored the sky. Pingo said, \"These wonderful lights are the northern lights. It's fun to watch them.\" Elsa and Jack gazed at the sky as if they were mesmerized. One night, the children stayed in Pingo's nest. They drank hot chocolate together and talked about how beautiful it was to live in the polar regions. Pingo said, \"In the polar regions, friendship and cooperation are very important. Because in these tough conditions, we have to support 