// //            engText: "Once upon a time, in the icy lands of Antarctica, there lived a little penguin named Pingo. Pingo was different from other penguins because he was always seeking adventure. His biggest dream was to see something other than ice and snow. Pingo often went on excursions to discover new things in this vast white world where he lived with his mother and father. One day, Pingo and his best friend Lila discovered a cave hidden between giant icebergs. This cave was more mysterious and fascinating than anything they had ever seen before. Their hearts were pounding with excitement. As Pingo walked deeper into the cave, he suddenly saw a bright light. This light was coming from the darkest corner of the cave. As they approached the source of the light, they found a massive door with shimmering letters that read 'Land of Ice Cream.' 'The Land of Ice Cream?' Pingo shouted. 'What does that mean, Lila?' Lila was just as surprised as Pingo. 'I don't know, Pingo, but there must be something wonderful behind this door. Let's see!' The two little penguins pushed the door open and went inside. They couldn't believe their eyes at the sight. In front of them was a world full of colorful ice creams. Ice cream cones hung from the trees, and the petals of flowers were covered in ice cream cream. Everywhere, there were different flavors of ice cream: chocolate, strawberry, vanilla, pistachio, banana, and many more. Pingo and Lila began walking through the ice creams. Suddenly, they heard the sound of children's laughter around them. Soon, they met a group of children. When the children saw Pingo and Lila, they welcomed them with great joy and joined them. 'Hello! My name is Ali,' said one child. 'This is the Land of Ice Cream. We discovered it a while ago.' 'What a wonderful place!' Pingo said excitedly. 'What do you do here?' Ali answered with a smile, 'We can do everything here! We build castles from ice cream, swim in ice cream rivers, and most importantly, eat as much ice cream as we want!' Pingo and Lila spent their time in this magical land with Ali and his friends. First, they climbed a hill covered with chocolate ice cream and slid down from it. Then they swam in a river filled with pistachio and caramel ice creams. Every ice cream flavor led them to a different adventure. Days passed, and Pingo, Lila, Ali, and the other children enjoyed every moment they spent in the Land of Ice Cream. But eventually, it was time for Pingo and Lila to return home. Like the other children, Pingo and Lila didn't want to leave this magical place, but they realized they missed their families. One morning, Pingo and Lila said goodbye to Ali and the other children and headed for the door. Ali hugged Pingo and said, 'You can always come back here, Pingo. The door will always be open.' Pingo smiled and said, 'Thank you, Ali. I will never forget this adventure.' When they passed through the door and exited the cave, they returned to the cold of Antarctica. But this time, their hearts were warm because they had experienced an unforgettable adventure. Pingo turned to Lila and said, 'This will be our secret. But maybe one day, we can show this place to our other penguin friends.' Lila smiled and said, 'Yes, maybe. But for now, let's keep it just between us.' Pingo and Lila returned home without ever losing their spirit of adventure. In the cold and white world of Antarctica, they carried a mystery filled with sweet memories of ice cream. And Pingo continued to live every day in search of new adventures, because he knew that the world was always full of new surprises to discover. The magical adventure of Penguin Pingo and his friends remained an unforgettable memory in their hearts. The sweet and cheerful world of the Land of Ice Cream would always be a place that Pingo and his friends would remember. Maybe one day, other adventurous penguins would find this hidden door and have their own ice cream land adventures. Because imagination and the spirit of discovery always open new doors and make the world a more colorful place.",
