// //             engText: "Once upon a time, in the vast, ice-covered polar regions, lived a cute and brave penguin. His name was Penguin Pingo. Pingo, with his bright white belly and cute blue hat, was loved by everyone. Pingo's biggest dream was to discover other creatures living in the polar regions and make friends with them. One day, a ship stopped near the glaciers where Pingo lived. There were children who got off this ship. The children had come to explore the animals and nature in the polar regions, and when they met Pingo, they immediately became friends. One of these children was named Elsa, and the other was Jack. Elsa said, \"Hello Pingo! We came here to discover the animals and nature in the polar regions.\" Pingo smiled, \"Great! I want to introduce you to my wonderful friends here. Come on, let's go on an adventure together!\" First, Pingo took the children on a walk over the glaciers. After a while, a polar bear with white fur and cute black eyes appeared. Pingo said, \"This is my friend Boris, he is a very kind bear.\" Boris said, \"Welcome! The polar regions are a magical place. Here, we always help each other,\" and waved his big paws to the children. Elsa and Jack loved Boris's huge but friendly appearance. Then, they encountered a family of seals. The mother seal was playing on the ice with her pups. Pingo said, \"This is my seal family. They are excellent swimmers.\" Jack watched in admiration, \"Wow! They swim so fast.\" As they continued their walk, the sky began to darken, and the northern lights colored the sky. Pingo said, \"These wonderful lights are the northern lights. It's fun to watch them.\" Elsa and Jack gazed at the sky as if they were mesmerized. One night, the children stayed in Pingo's nest. They drank hot chocolate together and talked about how beautiful it was to live in the polar regions. Pingo said, \"In the polar regions, friendship and cooperation are very important. Because in these tough conditions, we have to support each other.\" The next day, Pingo and the children encountered a group of seabirds. The leader of the birds, a seagull named Stella, sang fun songs to the children. Elsa and Jack danced to Stella's cheerful melodies. As the days passed, Pingo and the children met many more animals living in the polar regions: narwhals, walruses, and snowy owls. Each one taught the children about survival in the polar regions and the importance of friendship. Finally, it was time for Elsa and Jack to return home. As they said goodbye, Pingo said, \"The time we spent here was very special to me. I am very happy to have met you. Remember, true friendship is always with you.\" Elsa and Jack said, \"We will never forget you, Pingo. We will meet again one day,\" and hugged each other tightly. Thus, Penguin Pingo and the children left behind an unforgettable adventure. The time they spent in the polar regions taught them a lot about animals and showed them how valuable true friendship is.",
